{
  "doc_id": "4219",
  "text": "Mutants decreased susceptibility to R. solanacearum. Based on the senescence-specific characterization of SAG12, an autoregulatory senescence inhibition system (P SAG12 -IPT) has been explored by fusing the SAG12 promoter (PSAG12) to a cytokinin-biosynthesizing enzyme-isopentenyl transferase (IPT) [CITATION_1] . This fusion activates the expression of IPT at the onset of senescence and subsequently increases the cytokinin levels which, in turn, delays the decay of plant senescence [CITATION_2] . This technology has been successfully applied in practical applications in many plant species and is approaching commercialization [CITATION_3] . Various SAG12 orthologs genes with similar functions have beed identified in a variety of plant species including rice, B. napus, sweet potato and tobacco [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Similar to Arabidopsis SAG12, rice P SAG39 -IPT transgenic plants displayed a delayed leaf senescence phenotype and greater number of emerged panicles, suggesting the homologs function as Arabidopsis SAG12 [CITATION_9] . Similarly, in rubber tree (Hevea brasiliensis), there are 17 Arabidopsis SAG12 orthologs (HbSAG12H1-17) with HbSAG12H1 displayed the same expression pattern as senescence-associated genes, indicating that HbSAG12H1 can also act as a molecular marker to study the leaf senescence mechanism of Hevea [CITATION_10] . Subsequently, [CITATION_11] used HbSAG12H1 as the indicator to successfully identify six new PLCP genes, i.e., HbRD21B, HbRD21E, HbRD21F, HbCEP1, HbXBCP3L, and HbRD19B by deep sequencing of the senescence rubber leaf transcriptome, suggesting that these PLCPs may play important roles in leaf senescence [CITATION_12] . In addition, the individual dark treatment of Arabidopsis leaves (8 weeks old) showed that the leaf senescence program was induced to start, and the activities of many PLCPs were increased, among which RD21A and AALP displayed the highest induction in senescing leaves [CITATION_13] . By phenotypic analysis of the aalp-1 and rd21A-1/aalp-1 mutants, fewer senescent leaves were identified and senescence was delayed than wild type, indicating that AALP may be helpful to the senescence process of plants [CITATION_14] .",
